item.title: CVE-2020-7880|2024-08-04T09:41:01.881Z -- douzone -- neors
item.description: The vulnerabilty was discovered in ActiveX module related to NeoRS remote support program. This issue allows an remote attacker to download and execute remote file. It is because of improper parameter validation of StartNeoRS function in ActiveX.
